{{nihongo|'''Kiiti Morita'''|森田 紀一|Morita Kiichi|February 11, 1915 &ndash; August 4, 1995}} was a Japanese [[mathematician]] working in [[algebra]] and [[topology]].
Born in [[Hamamatsu]], he received his Ph.D. from the [[Osaka Prefecture University|University of Osaka]] in 1950 and was professor at the [[University of Tsukuba]].
He introduced the concepts now known as [[Morita equivalence]] and [[Morita duality]] which were given wide circulation in the 1960s by [[Hyman Bass]] in a series of lectures. The [[Morita conjectures]] on [[normal space|normal topological spaces]] are also named after him.
